OL,3,C'It's our lifeline': Deaf and blind
OL,4,Ccentre at risk of closure
OL,6,FMoreen Wood is a centre user. Four
OL,7,Fgenerations of her family are deaf.
OL,9,FShe said: "For me, this place is like
OL,10,Fa second home. When I'm in the deaf
OL,11,Fclub, I can just be normal. Out there,
OL,12,FI'm not seen as normal.
OL,14,F"For hearing people, the community is
OL,15,Fwhere you live. For deaf people, the
OL,16,Fcommunity is the deaf centre and if it
OL,17,Fcloses it will be a complete normal."
